
# OvenCraft Pizzaria



OvenCraft Pizzaria is a simple pizza ordering application built using Python's `tkinter` library. This application allows users to select their desired pizza type from a menu and place an order. It provides an intuitive and interactive user interface for ordering pizzas.

## Features

- User-friendly GUI for ordering pizzas.
- Selection of pizza type from a dropdown menu.
- Ability to place an order and receive a confirmation message.
- Use of `PIL` (Python Imaging Library) to display background images.

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository to your local machine using `git clone https://github.com/your-username/pizza-ordering-app.git`.
2. Navigate to the project directory: `cd pizza-ordering-app`.
3. Run the application: `python pizza_app.py`.

## Requirements

- Python 3.x
- `tkinter` library (included with most standard Python installations)
- `PIL` (Python Imaging Library) for image support

## Usage

1. Run the pizza ordering application by executing `pizza_app.py` using Python.
2. The application window will display the welcome message and a background image.
3. Select your desired pizza type from the dropdown menu.
4. Click the "Place Order" button to submit your pizza order.
5. A confirmation message will pop up, indicating that your order has been placed.

